<h2>Welcome to The Countdown Tracker</h2>

<p>The Countdown Tracker is a web app created to allow MCs of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Powered_by_the_Apocalypse">Powered by the Apocalypse</a> 
games to to track and share Countdown Clocks.  It was inspired by watching MCs freehand scribble Countdown Clocks on Google Hangouts and thinking that there 
needed to be another way. 

<p>The Tracker comes in two varieties.  A digital version modeled after the Countdown Clocks in  
<a href="http://www.drivethrurpg.com/product/171286/The-Sprawl----MIDNIGHT">The Sprawl</a>, and an analog 
version modeled aver the ones that appear in the rest of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Powered_by_the_Apocalypse">Powered by the Apocalypse</a> games.

 <h3>How it works:</h3>

<p>The MC clicks one of the <b>Create...</b> buttons below to create a new Countdown Controller. 

<p>They then share the link to The Big Board with their players (via Email, TXT, SMS, etc), and use the
Countdown Controller screen to manage their game's Countdown Clocks.  Modifications made to the clocks 
are instantly transmitted to the Big Board through the magic of <a href="http://lmgtfy.com/?q=websockets">WebSockets</a>.  

<h3>Important Note:</h3>

<p>Your Countdown Contoller it is identified by a unique URL.  That URL identifies you to the database as 
the owner of your Clocks.  You are the <i>only</i> person in the universe that knows it.  If you lose it, 
it's gone forever.  There is no way to get it back. So Bookmark it, email it to yourself, write it on a PostIt 
and stick it on your monitor.  Do whatever it takes to keep track of it.  

<p>(Actually, if you lose it, its no big deal. You can just make a new one). 

<h3>Chromecast</h3>
The MC screen has Google Cast support baked in, so if you have a Chromecast available you can cast away!  
If a Chromecast receiver is detected, the Google Cast icon will appear in the upper left hand corner of the page .  If one is detected 
the icon will appear .  If no Chromecast is detected, the 
icon will not appear.  Click the icon to connect to the Chromecast.

